  "description": "The key feature of this model is a bright and unusual design in retro style, thanks to which this refrigerator can become the main highlight in the kitchen. In technical terms, we have a classic two-chamber refrigerator with a total useful volume of 258 liters. A relatively small freezer with a volume of 57 liters is placed on top. It is equipped with a separate access door, is capable of freezing up to 3 kg of fresh food per day, and also boasts an extremely low maintained temperature — down to -32 °C. The volume of the refrigerating chamber Gunter&Hauer FN 275 R is 201 liters. The manufacturer provides support for the automatic defrost function, which eliminates the need for the owner to turn off and defrost the refrigerator manually. Also pay attention to the fact that the model has been assigned an A ++ energy class, and the average energy consumption claimed by the manufacturer per year is 197 kWh.",
